  "description": "Herman Bursie was a former consul and civil engineer from Gothenburg, Sweden, born on November 13, 1885 in Skövde to Colonel Herman B. and Christine Heftye. He was married to Ingegerd Söderberg in 1921 and had two children. He completed his high school studies in 1905 and his civil engineering studies in 1909. He worked abroad in the engineering field from 1910 to 1917 and later worked for SKF in various positions, including assistant manager and engineer. He also served as temporary Norwegian consul in Milan from 1922 to 1924 and as Swedish consul there from 1929 to 1937. He was involved in various organizations, such as SA Ing. Maselli & Co. and the Swedish Association in Milan, and received awards such as the Royal Order of Vasa and the Royal Patriotic Society's Gold Medal. He passed away on [please provide if available]."
